01:11.927 --> 01:14.959
Sorry, I didn't even
notice you there!

01:14.961 --> 01:15.919
No, no, no, no,
don't apologize!

01:15.921 --> 01:17.224
Don't apologize!

01:17.226 --> 01:18.223
Continue!

01:18.225 --> 01:19.183
Keep dancing.

01:20.183 --> 01:22.140
I must look crazy.

01:22.142 --> 01:23.138
It's just great
to see somebody

01:23.140 --> 01:24.752
loving the rain
so much.

01:24.754 --> 01:26.095
Well, don't you
just love it?

01:26.097 --> 01:26.940
No.

01:26.942 --> 01:27.900
What?

01:27.902 --> 01:29.244
No!

01:29.246 --> 01:30.703
You hate the rain?

01:30.705 --> 01:32.009
Yes!

01:32.971 --> 01:34.505
How could anyone
hate the rain?

01:34.507 --> 01:36.002
Well, I'm afraid
I might shrink.

01:37.387 --> 01:40.879
No, you have to
become one with it.

01:40.881 --> 01:42.761
Just melt into it.

01:42.763 --> 01:43.798
Don't resist.

01:43.800 --> 01:45.026
Oh!

01:45.028 --> 01:46.063
Ah!

01:46.065 --> 01:47.330
Ah, it's cold!

01:48.907 --> 01:50.556
Phew!

01:50.558 --> 01:52.478
Ah...

01:57.355 --> 01:59.004
Can I have one?

01:59.006 --> 02:01.733
Uh... yeah.

02:06.263 --> 02:07.606
Got a lighter too?

02:07.608 --> 02:09.526
Yeah, I do.

02:11.409 --> 02:12.406
Oh, be careful.

02:12.408 --> 02:14.709
Don't burn yourself.

02:14.711 --> 02:16.631
Got it lit?

02:19.819 --> 02:21.084
So you're that writer,
aren't you?

02:21.086 --> 02:23.006
Yes.

02:25.502 --> 02:26.229
From New York, right?

02:26.231 --> 02:28.073
Yes.

02:28.075 --> 02:29.340
Can I ask you
a question?

02:29.342 --> 02:30.531
Yes.

02:30.533 --> 02:33.564
Why would you leave New York
to come to this hole?

02:33.566 --> 02:34.639
I needed a change
of scenery.

02:34.641 --> 02:37.097
But New York...

02:37.099 --> 02:39.516
I mean, I would do anything
to visit New York!

02:39.518 --> 02:41.705
To... soak in
the architecture,

02:41.707 --> 02:43.165
the people...

02:43.167 --> 02:45.200
see the shows
on Broadway.

02:45.202 --> 02:47.004
Ha-have...
Do we...

02:47.006 --> 02:48.924
do we know
each other?

02:48.926 --> 02:50.153
No.

02:50.155 --> 02:52.034
No, but everyone knows
who you are.

02:52.036 --> 02:54.223
You're the famous author
living in Goose Cove.

02:54.225 --> 02:56.145
Yeah.

02:57.797 --> 03:00.444
I gotta go.

03:00.446 --> 03:02.364
Don't tell anyone
I smoke, okay?

03:02.366 --> 03:04.821
Okay.

03:04.823 --> 03:06.895
Goodbye, Mr. Author.

03:06.897 --> 03:08.432
I hope I'll see you
again sometime.

03:08.434 --> 03:10.354
Me too.

03:11.391 --> 03:12.348
What's your name?

03:12.350 --> 03:14.308
Nola.

04:08.606 --> 04:10.025
<i>Sommerdale Police,
how can I help you?</i>

04:10.027 --> 04:12.598
It's Deborah Cooper
in Side Creek Lane.

04:12.600 --> 04:13.519
Uh... I...

04:13.521 --> 04:15.823
Come quick! Right now!

04:15.825 --> 04:17.283
<i>You heard prowlers
again, Mrs. Cooper?</i>

04:17.285 --> 04:18.512
No, no, it's a girl!

04:18.514 --> 04:21.545
She's being chased
in the woods by a man!

04:21.547 --> 04:22.774
I-I was making an apple pie,

04:22.776 --> 04:25.884
heard a scream,
and looked out the screen door.

04:25.886 --> 04:27.343
She was wearing a red dress.

04:27.345 --> 04:28.649
She's...

04:28.651 --> 04:30.339
she's running
through the forest,

04:30.341 --> 04:31.644
and he's chasing her.

04:31.646 --> 04:32.681
<i>I'm sending
a patrol car over</i>

04:32.683 --> 04:34.102
<i>right away, Mrs. Cooper.</i>

04:34.104 --> 04:35.139
<i>Please stay where you are.</i>

04:55.339 --> 04:57.180
Hurry!

05:54.577 --> 05:59.577
Subtitles by explosiveskull

07:18.110 --> 07:20.604
<i>Anyone who says
success is overrated</i>

07:20.606 --> 07:21.871
<i>isn't doing it right.</i>

07:21.873 --> 07:24.022
<i>This is me, Marcus Goldman.</i>

07:24.024 --> 07:27.247
<i>At the age of 26,
I had written my first novel,</i>

07:27.249 --> 07:28.629
<i>which sold
over a million copies,</i>

07:28.631 --> 07:32.355
<i>propelling me onto
everyone's must-read list.</i>

07:32.357 --> 07:33.622
<i>I was suddenly a celebrity.</i>

07:33.624 --> 07:35.388
<i>My book, "G is for Goldstein,"</i>

07:35.390 --> 07:37.077
<i>was heralded far and wide</i>

07:37.079 --> 07:39.344
<i>as the work of an original
and rare talent,</i>

07:39.346 --> 07:41.686
<i>even by the toughest
of New York critics.</i>

07:41.688 --> 07:43.798
<i>Suddenly, everything I said</i>

07:43.800 --> 07:46.025
<i>was of interest and hilarious.</i>

07:46.027 --> 07:48.367
<i>No more dining on ramen.</i>

07:48.369 --> 07:50.594
<i>It's now Peking duck
at Mr. Chow,</i>

07:50.596 --> 07:52.284
<i>prepared by the chef himself.</i>

07:52.286 --> 07:55.356
<i>No more squinting
to watch the big game,</i>

07:55.358 --> 07:57.775
<i>but enjoying it
on a 110-inch plasma screen</i>

07:57.777 --> 07:59.157
<i>with Douglas Claren,</i>

07:59.159 --> 08:00.387
<i>my agent.</i>

08:00.389 --> 08:04.188
<i>I even hired a secretary
named Denise,</i>

08:04.190 --> 08:06.838
<i>who I think might have had
a little crush on me.</i>

08:06.840 --> 08:08.028
<i>For the first six months</i>

08:08.030 --> 08:09.987
<i>after the publication
of my book,</i>

08:09.989 --> 08:12.674
<i>life was a writer's wet dream.</i>

08:12.676 --> 08:14.287
<i>There were book signings</i>

08:14.289 --> 08:16.207
<i>and a contract
for my next two novels,</i>

08:16.209 --> 08:17.935
<i>with a little advance
thrown in there</i>

08:17.937 --> 08:19.241
<i>for good measure.</i>

08:19.243 --> 08:20.738
Wow. Thank you!

08:20.740 --> 08:22.850
<i>Success does have
its drawbacks,</i>

08:22.852 --> 08:25.347
<i>like what to say
when someone asks you...</i>

08:25.349 --> 08:26.921
So what's
your next book about?

08:26.923 --> 08:28.418
<i>It had been over a year</i>

08:28.420 --> 08:30.838
<i>since the publication
of my first book,</i>

08:30.840 --> 08:32.988
<i>and I still had not written
a single word</i>

08:32.990 --> 08:34.524
<i>of the next one.</i>

08:34.525 --> 08:35.751
<i>Not that I didn't try.</i>

08:35.754 --> 08:37.519
<i>Inspiration had abandoned me,</i>

08:37.520 --> 08:39.056
<i>and I was scared shitless,</i>

08:39.058 --> 08:42.434
<i>because where I come from,
failure is not an option.</i>

08:42.437 --> 08:44.085
<i>Even in high school,</i>

08:44.087 --> 08:46.505
<i>Marcus Goldman always found
some way to come out a winner.</i>

08:46.507 --> 08:47.695
<i>I figured out pretty early</i>

08:47.697 --> 08:50.268
<i>the best way
to stand out in a crowd</i>

08:50.270 --> 08:53.918
<i>was to pick the right crowd
to stand out in.</i>

08:56.260 --> 08:57.833
<i>My strategy was so successful,</i>

08:57.835 --> 09:01.634
<i>I soon became known as
"Marcus the Magnificent."</i>

09:01.636 --> 09:03.900
<i>See, the trouble is,
the more you win,</i>

09:03.902 --> 09:06.166
<i>the more terrifying it is
to lose,</i>

09:06.168 --> 09:08.930
<i>and I was on the verge
of losing everything.</i>

09:08.932 --> 09:10.659
<i>I tried everything
to get unblocked.</i>

09:10.661 --> 09:13.539
<i>I escaped to the desert
for solitude,</i>

09:13.541 --> 09:17.570
<i>to reconnect
with my inner voice.</i>

09:17.572 --> 09:19.145
<i>I even returned
to my old room in New Jersey</i>

09:19.147 --> 09:20.220
<i>hoping for inspiration...</i>

09:20.222 --> 09:22.601
Shh!
He's writing!

09:22.603 --> 09:24.482
<i>The trouble with
being hailed as a genius</i>

09:24.484 --> 09:26.249
<i>is that now
everything you write</i>

09:26.251 --> 09:28.169
<i>is expected to be
a literary gem,</i>

09:28.171 --> 09:32.355
<i>some timeless insight
into the human condition.</i>

09:32.357 --> 09:34.159
<i>The pressure
to live up to the hype</i>

09:34.161 --> 09:35.311
<i>froze me.</i>

09:35.313 --> 09:37.269
<i>There was only one person
I knew</i>

09:37.271 --> 09:38.921
<i>who could help me
cut through the bullshit</i>

09:38.923 --> 09:40.726
<i>and bring me back to reality,</i>

09:40.728 --> 09:42.915
<i>Harry Quebert,</i>

09:42.917 --> 09:45.602
<i>best-selling author,
my former college professor,</i>

09:45.604 --> 09:49.022
<i>and one of the greatest writers
of the 20th century.</i>

10:05.726 --> 10:07.759
Oh, Marcus!

10:07.761 --> 10:09.295
Is this really you?

10:09.297 --> 10:10.524
<i>Yeah, yeah.</i>

10:10.526 --> 10:11.944
- It is?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

10:11.946 --> 10:13.519
- Incredible.
- <i>Yeah.</i>

10:13.521 --> 10:14.786
I know, I'm, uh...

10:14.788 --> 10:16.323
sorry, Harry.

10:16.325 --> 10:18.050
I've been completely
off the grid.

10:18.052 --> 10:19.548
<i>I haven't heard from you</i>

10:19.550 --> 10:21.429
<i>since you became a star.</i>

10:21.431 --> 10:23.234
I tried to call you
about a month ago.

10:23.236 --> 10:24.233
Your assistant said

10:24.235 --> 10:26.153
you weren't taking calls
from anybody.

10:26.155 --> 10:28.226
<i>I'm, uh...</i>

10:28.228 --> 10:30.300
<i>totally blocked, Harry.</i>

10:30.302 --> 10:32.604
<i>It's been over a year,
and I got nothing...</i>

10:32.606 --> 10:34.601
except a deadline
I'm not gonna meet.

10:34.603 --> 10:36.636
<i>Yeah.</i>

10:36.638 --> 10:38.326
<i>That second one
is always the toughest.</i>

10:38.328 --> 10:39.478
Yeah.

10:39.480 --> 10:41.282
<i>A lot of expectation
out there...</i>

10:41.284 --> 10:43.164
and creativity
just does not thrive

10:43.166 --> 10:45.122
when there is a deadline.

10:45.124 --> 10:46.274
It's like sex,

10:46.276 --> 10:48.233
but there's no
little blue pill for a writer.

10:48.235 --> 10:49.999
You know, why don't you
come to me?

10:50.001 --> 10:51.650
<i>Just get out of New York.</i>

10:51.652 --> 10:53.148
<i>Have a change
of scenery, you know?</i>

10:53.150 --> 10:54.108
Really?

10:54.110 --> 10:55.183
<i>Go for a run on the beach,</i>

10:55.185 --> 10:57.142
<i>get your creative juices
going.</i>

10:57.144 --> 10:59.446
You know?

10:59.448 --> 11:00.943
Let inspiration come to you.

11:00.945 --> 11:02.441
Okay.

11:02.443 --> 11:03.670
<i>Yeah.</i>

11:03.672 --> 11:07.049
It's a deal. I'll, uh...
I'll see you this weekend.

11:07.051 --> 11:08.971
<i>All right.</i>

11:16.996 --> 11:18.607
<i>I loved driving to Maine.</i>

11:18.609 --> 11:20.604
<i>I knew Sommerdale well,</i>

11:20.606 --> 11:24.368
<i>having visited Harry there
several times as a student.</i>

11:24.370 --> 11:27.247
<i>I loved this little town
forgotten by time,</i>

11:27.249 --> 11:28.707
<i>its churches,</i>

11:28.709 --> 11:31.855
<i>peaceful neighborhoods
of painted wooden houses,</i>

11:31.857 --> 11:33.314
<i>the shops,</i>

11:33.316 --> 11:36.770
<i>and Clark's,
the town's historic diner</i>

11:36.772 --> 11:38.115
<i>where Harry and I would eat</i>

11:38.117 --> 11:40.457
<i>and spend hours
talking about life,</i>

11:40.459 --> 11:42.799
<i>and books, and...</i>

11:42.801 --> 11:45.336
<i>and what it meant
to be a writer.</i>

11:48.830 --> 11:50.671
<i>Harry was living
a few miles away,</i>

11:50.673 --> 11:53.167
<i>isolated amongst
the tranquil wilderness</i>

11:53.169 --> 11:54.819
<i>of the coastal forest</i>

11:54.821 --> 11:57.736
<i>in a beautiful stone
and solid pine house</i>

11:57.738 --> 11:59.350
<i>with an ocean view</i>

11:59.352 --> 12:03.077
<i>and a deck overlooking
an endless beach.</i>

12:24.197 --> 12:26.153
Marcus the Magnificent!

12:26.155 --> 12:27.689
Hey, Harry.

12:27.691 --> 12:28.764
You made it!

12:28.766 --> 12:30.184
- How are you, man?
- It's good to see you!

12:30.186 --> 12:31.759
It's good
to see you too!

12:31.761 --> 12:33.180
Welcome back.

12:33.182 --> 12:34.985
It's good
to see you, man.

12:34.987 --> 12:36.405
This is new.

12:36.407 --> 12:37.596
This is new,
it looks good.

12:37.598 --> 12:39.518
I painted it.

12:40.209 --> 12:41.090
Welcome.

12:41.092 --> 12:42.511
Please.
Thanks, man.

12:42.513 --> 12:44.278
Oh, God,
it's good to be back.

12:56.606 --> 12:59.062
First, get good
at being patient.

12:59.064 --> 13:01.327
The more patient you are,
the more likely it is

13:01.329 --> 13:03.631
your muse will
pay you a visit.

13:03.633 --> 13:05.359
But you know me, Harry.

13:05.361 --> 13:07.855
Patience has never
been my strong suit.

13:07.857 --> 13:09.545
Especially now.

13:09.547 --> 13:12.387
And stop trying to write
the Great American Novel.

13:12.389 --> 13:14.191
That will only paralyze you.

13:14.193 --> 13:15.497
You can't write from fear.

13:15.499 --> 13:16.802
Then what do I
write from?

13:16.804 --> 13:20.181
'Cause right now, fear's
the only thing I got.

13:20.183 --> 13:22.716
That and terror.

13:22.718 --> 13:25.020
You have to write
what matters to you.

13:25.022 --> 13:27.286
Screw all the voices
in your head,

13:27.288 --> 13:28.553
the ones judging you,

13:28.555 --> 13:31.625
telling you what you should
or should not write about.

13:31.627 --> 13:35.004
Go with your gut,
the idea that excites you.

13:35.006 --> 13:35.695
And what if
I change my mind

13:35.697 --> 13:37.999
halfway through?

13:38.001 --> 13:40.073
You can always
change your mind,

13:40.075 --> 13:41.609
go in a different direction.

13:41.611 --> 13:42.953
The point is to write,

13:42.955 --> 13:44.143
pen to paper.

13:44.145 --> 13:48.137
The words are immaterial,
it's all about the idea.

13:48.139 --> 13:50.095
Is that helping?

13:50.097 --> 13:51.286
It's pretty
simple, yeah...

13:51.288 --> 13:52.553
No, it's not helping.

13:52.555 --> 13:53.398
He needs
some inspiration.

13:53.400 --> 13:54.281
What can you
say to him?

13:54.283 --> 13:55.356
Oh, well,

13:55.358 --> 13:57.506
it helps if you sit
where he's sitting.

13:57.508 --> 13:59.429
Just for good luck.

14:00.234 --> 14:01.192
Thanks, Jenny.

14:01.194 --> 14:03.419
Thank you, Jenny.

14:03.421 --> 14:05.342
Ah, yes...

14:16.138 --> 14:17.481
Okay, I'm off.

14:17.483 --> 14:19.746
My last class
is around 5:00,

14:19.748 --> 14:21.897
so let's have cocktails
on the deck

14:21.899 --> 14:23.202
at 6:00 sharp, okay?

14:23.204 --> 14:24.124
Okay, great.

14:24.126 --> 14:25.122
Yeah, listen, if I'm not here,

14:25.124 --> 14:26.389
my body will probably
wash up on shore

14:26.391 --> 14:27.503
in a few days' time.

14:27.505 --> 14:28.848
Not going well?

14:28.850 --> 14:29.923
No.

14:29.925 --> 14:31.151
No, are you kidding?
It's extraordinary.

14:31.153 --> 14:33.378
It's, uh, yeah,
completely unpredictable.

14:33.380 --> 14:35.416
Can't wait to find out
what happens next.

14:39.140 --> 14:40.713
You haven't written
anything at all.

14:40.715 --> 14:43.247
Not... not
entirely true.

14:43.249 --> 14:45.359
I, uh... texted Sofia.

14:45.361 --> 14:47.394
- Well, sexted her.
- Hmm.

14:47.396 --> 14:49.891
That's probably the appropriate
nomenclature, but, uh...

14:49.893 --> 14:50.966
it's actually the best writing

14:50.968 --> 14:52.425
I've done all year.

14:52.427 --> 14:55.113
All right.

14:55.115 --> 14:58.569
Just tell me
how you did it, man.

14:58.571 --> 15:00.259
Oh, you sat in a diner
day after day?

15:00.261 --> 15:02.524
You wrote a masterpiece
in one summer?

15:02.526 --> 15:03.215
Okay.

15:03.217 --> 15:06.095
Write what interests you.

15:06.097 --> 15:07.938
Or yet, better yet, you know,
just don't write at all.

15:07.940 --> 15:10.089
Live.

15:10.091 --> 15:11.164
Don't make...

15:11.166 --> 15:13.660
life about your work.

15:13.662 --> 15:15.812
Or you'll end up
like me.

15:17.847 --> 15:18.882
6:00, drinks.

15:18.884 --> 15:20.804
Yeah.

15:31.940 --> 15:32.860
So, what's the next

15:32.862 --> 15:34.857
Marcus Goldman
masterpiece about?

15:35.741 --> 15:36.776
Give us a little hint.

15:36.778 --> 15:37.698
Well, you know,
the writing process

15:37.700 --> 15:39.350
is a very fragile thing,

15:39.352 --> 15:41.577
you know, much,
much like an unborn child.

15:41.579 --> 15:44.610
It needs to incubate
until it's fully formed,

15:44.612 --> 15:47.375
and then,
much like childbirth itself,

15:47.377 --> 15:48.489
it can be a painful process
to see through...

15:49.873 --> 15:51.793
You're so full of shit.

16:08.459 --> 16:10.417
<i>How the hell did he do it?</i>

17:36.318 --> 17:37.391
Hey.

17:37.393 --> 17:40.847
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

17:40.849 --> 17:42.769
Oh, um...

17:44.843 --> 17:46.763
Just...

17:53.367 --> 17:55.439
What, are you
spying on me, Marcus?

17:55.441 --> 17:57.743
No, no, no,
Harry, I just, um...

17:57.745 --> 17:59.163
Um...

17:59.165 --> 18:01.199
You go through
my personal things?

18:01.201 --> 18:03.121
I'm s... I'm sorry.

18:10.685 --> 18:12.605
I'm sorry,
I shouldn't have opened it.

18:21.860 --> 18:25.201
She was someone I once knew.

18:26.469 --> 18:28.388
It's complicated.

18:31.768 --> 18:33.916
This needs to stay...

18:33.918 --> 18:35.838
between us.

18:38.526 --> 18:40.137
Do you understand me?

18:40.139 --> 18:42.018
Yeah.

18:42.020 --> 18:45.630
Yeah, you have
my word.

19:04.638 --> 19:05.903
Don't be a stranger.

19:05.905 --> 19:06.786
Yeah.

19:06.788 --> 19:08.708
Yeah, you too.

19:11.819 --> 19:12.623
Thanks again, Harry.

19:12.625 --> 19:14.545
Mm-hmm.

19:44.075 --> 19:44.840
<i>You listening?</i>

19:44.842 --> 19:46.377
Mm-hmm.

19:46.379 --> 19:48.604
Well, how are
things looking?

19:48.606 --> 19:50.217
<i>So, we got Joe Fryman,
the top litigator in the city,</i>

19:50.219 --> 19:51.983
<i>to review your contract
with Schmid and Hanson.</i>

19:51.985 --> 19:53.135
And?

19:53.137 --> 19:54.594
<i>You're totally screwed.</i>

19:54.596 --> 19:55.861
<i>Either you deliver up
a new draft</i>

19:55.863 --> 19:57.320
<i>by the agreed-upon date,</i>

19:57.322 --> 19:59.547
<i>or they take
everything you own.</i>

19:59.549 --> 20:02.159
Okay, what if I sign everything
over to my parents?

20:02.161 --> 20:04.118
Like, including the condo.

